babble.util

Class MethodSignature

  • java.lang.Object
    • babble.util.MethodSignature

  • public class MethodSignature
extends Object
    A signature for a Java method as a string. A signature can be constructed either from a compiled method or from a string matching a regular expression.
    The regular expression for a signature is 
        signature := return-type method-name '(' param-decl ')
    return-type := class-name
    method-name := java-identifier
    param-decl  := param-name':'param-type
    param-name  := java-identifier
    param-type  := class-name
    
    java-identifier is a string (one or more non-whitespace character)
    that is a valid identifier in Java language syntax
    
    class-name is also a string that is can be loaded by context
    class loader of current thread
    Author:
    pinaki poddar

        public String getArgumentName(int i)
        Gets the name of the i-th input argument. The argument names are available for if the owning method was compiled in Java 8 with -parameter option.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
